4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, the Department of Revenue
6 designs or has designed the "Helping Schools"
7 distinctive license plate.
8 This bill would create additional design
9 requirements the Department of Revenue must follow when
10 designing the "Helping Schools" distinctive license
11 plates.
12 This bill would also allow certain individuals
13 to receive a new "Helping Schools" distinctive license
14 plate at no cost once the new design requirements are
15 met.
16
17
18 A BILL
19 TO BE ENTITLED
20 AN ACT
21
22 Relating to distinctive license plates; to amend
23 Section 32-6-300, Code of Alabama 1975, to further provide for
24 the design requirements for the "Helping Schools" license
25 plates; and to authorize certain individuals to receive the
26 new design of the license plate at no cost.
27 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
28 Section 1. Section 32-6-300, Code of Alabama 1975, is
Page 1

Section 1. Section 32-6-300, Code of Alabama 1975, is
SB300 INTRODUCED
29 amended to read as follows:
30 "§32-6-300
31 (a) Owners of all motor vehicles who are residents of
32 Alabama, upon application to the judge of probate or
33 commissioner of licenses, complying with the state motor
34 vehicle laws relating to registration and licensing of motor
35 vehicles and payment of the regular license fee for plates as
36 provided by law for the motor vehicle, and the payment of an
37 additional annual fee of twenty dollars ($20), shall be issued
38 license plates which shall consist of a white background; bear
39 the words "Helping Schools." in red lettering; and contain a
40 drawing of a red apple, green book, and yellow ruler.
41 (b) The plates shall be issued, printed, and processed
42 in the same manner as other personalized plates are in this
43 chapter. The plates shall be valid for five years and shall be
44 replaced at the end of the period with either conventional
45 plates or other personalized plates, or with new "Helping
46 Schools" plates. Payment of the required motor vehicle license
47 fees and taxes for the years during which a new vehicle
48 license plate is not issued shall be evidenced as provided for
49 in Section 32-6-63. The State Department of Revenue shall
50 design, or have designed, design of the "Helping Schools"
51 plates shall be made in compliance with all laws and
52 regulations.
53 (c) For the registration year beginning January 1,
54 2027, only, an individual in possession of a "Helping Schools"
55 plate that was bought or renewed during the period of March 1,
56 2025, to December 31, 2026, the Department of Revenue shall
Page 2

2025, to December 31, 2026, the Department of Revenue shall
SB300 INTRODUCED
57 issue a new "Helping Schools" plate that meets the design
58 requirements of this section, and shall not charge a fee for
59 the replacement plate."
60 Section 2. This act shall become effective on January
61 1, 2027.
